  "prompt": "Can I directly get an admission in 12th (Arts) after 10th (Maharashtra)?",
  "response": "In Maharashtra, as in many other states in India, admission to the 12th grade typically follows the completion of the 11th grade. Generally, students who complete their 10th-grade education choose a stream\u2014such as Arts, Science, or Commerce\u2014and then proceed to study in that stream for both 11th and 12th grades (often referred to as Junior College). Directly admitting a student to 12th grade without completing 11th grade is usually not permitted due to the structured progression of the education system, which builds knowledge year by year.\n\nHowever, specific institutions or private study options might have different regulations. If you are considering alternative study paths, such as open schooling or a different educational board, it\u2019s important to research those options specifically. The Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education (MSBSHSE) typically requires completion of both 11th and 12th grades for the Higher Secondary Certificate (HSC).\n\nFor accurate guidance, you should directly contact the educational institutions you are interested in or consult with an educational advisor, particularly if there are unique circumstances regarding your academics.",
